The curent density–voltage (J-V) measurement of bifacial tandems with rear illumination was carried out using a Kithley 4200 source meter. A Xenon lamp solar simulator with AM 1.5G spectrum (100 mW cm−2) was used as front illumination. For the rear illumination, the second Xenon lamp solar simulator with AM 1.5G spectrum (0–100 mW cm−2) used to simulate the real albedo. The power density of the rear illumination was calibared by using a standard Si solar cell form Word PV scale. The area of the tandems was 0.09 cm2 (0.3 cm ×\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
